  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The local node alias (private key), nodes, and peers MUST be saved and restored between sessions (network state file/database). \n\nThe alias can be reset by manually deleting network state file/database. An option to reset alias from UI or CLI is NOT recommended; doing so resets the client's network and downgrades the nodes security by clearing it's ability to evaluate network trust.\n\nDependencies:\n- kademlia: maliciousness is inverse to availability\n- peer reputation\n- peer connection strategy\n\nEffects:\n- reduces network churn\n- reduces convergence overhead from major network power events (splits)\n- tofu: trust on first-use\n- [future] reduced overhead for DHT\n",
